00:00:00.307 --> 00:00:02.385
 The Master of Scarlett and Hensle gave them 

00:00:02.385 --> 00:00:04.369
 a system of linear equations to solve. 

00:00:04.369 --> 00:00:05.922
 Each of them has taken several steps that have led 

00:00:05.922 --> 00:00:07.825
 to the systems shown in the table below. 

00:00:07.825 --> 00:00:08.788
 So, this is the system of teacher's equations. 

00:00:08.788 --> 00:00:11.308
 She received Scarlett after she had done several steps. 

00:00:11.308 --> 00:00:12.909
 That's got Hanks. 

00:00:12.909 --> 00:00:14.106
 Which one has received a system, 

00:00:14.106 --> 00:00:17.019
 equivalent to the teacher's system? 

00:00:17.019 --> 00:00:17.681
 And just to remember, 

00:00:17.681 --> 00:00:19.701
 equivalent to a given system is, 

00:00:19.701 --> 00:00:21.303
 at least for our purpose, 

00:00:21.303 --> 00:00:23.822
 a system that has the same solution, 

00:00:23.822 --> 00:00:25.320
 or the same set of decisions as the one given. 

00:00:25.320 --> 00:00:26.898
 If there is a precisely defined pair (x, y) 

00:00:26.898 --> 00:00:28.268
 which satisfies the teacher's system, 

00:00:28.268 --> 00:00:31.160
 in order for Scarlett's system to be equivalent to that system, 

00:00:31.160 --> 00:00:33.458
 it must have the same solution. 

00:00:33.458 --> 00:00:34.967
 Let's look at it. 

00:00:34.967 --> 00:00:36.406
 Scarlett ... Let's see 

00:00:36.406 --> 00:00:39.159
 whether we can connect them. 

00:00:39.159 --> 00:00:43.465
 Her second equation here, 

00:00:43.465 --> 00:00:45.473
 this is interesting, 

00:00:45.473 --> 00:00:49.235
 its second equation 14x minus 7u is equal to 2, 

00:00:49.235 --> 00:00:50.813
 here the teacher has an equation 

00:00:50.813 --> 00:00:54.133
 14x minus 7u is equal to 7. 

00:00:54.133 --> 00:00:56.745
 This is interesting because the ratio 

00:00:56.745 --> 00:00:59.334
 between x and y is the same, 

00:00:59.334 --> 00:01:01.354
 but then the permanent member, 

00:01:01.354 --> 00:01:04.744
 the permanent member will be different. 

00:01:04.744 --> 00:01:06.114
 And I say, 

00:01:06.114 --> 00:01:09.109
 that this is already telling us that Scarlett's system 

00:01:09.109 --> 00:01:11.629
 is not equivalent to that of the teacher. 

00:01:11.629 --> 00:01:14.624
 You're probably wondering how can I say that? 

00:01:14.624 --> 00:01:16.690
 If you write these two equations 

00:01:16.690 --> 00:01:19.128
 in the type of tilt-intersection, 

00:01:19.128 --> 00:01:20.590
 you will see the reason, because the ratio 

00:01:20.590 --> 00:01:23.895
 between members x and y is the same. 

00:01:23.895 --> 00:01:25.637
 You will have the same slope, 

00:01:25.637 --> 00:01:27.273
 but you will have a different cross with the y y axis. 

00:01:27.273 --> 00:01:28.690
 In fact, we can find it. 

00:01:28.690 --> 00:01:30.072
 This equation is here 

00:01:30.072 --> 00:01:32.927
 can be written as ... Let's see, 

00:01:32.927 --> 00:01:35.133
 if we pull out 14x on both sides, 

00:01:35.133 --> 00:01:38.761
 we get minus 7th 

00:01:38.761 --> 00:01:41.721
 is equal 

00:01:41.721 --> 00:01:45.892
 to minus 14x plus 7 

00:01:45.892 --> 00:01:47.749
 and we can divide both sides to minus 7. 

00:01:47.749 --> 00:01:52.485
 We get y is equal to 2x minus 1, and that is ... 

00:01:52.485 --> 00:01:54.321
 I just did this algebraically. 

00:01:54.321 --> 00:01:55.643
 The right is this and I can even try 

00:01:55.643 --> 00:01:58.046
 to draw it. 

